{"indexed": {"date-parts": [[2025, 8, 23]], "date-time": "2025-08-23T05:16:28Z", "timestamp": 1755926188738, "version": "3.41.0"}, "reference-count": 69, "publisher": "Wiley", "issue": "12", "license": [{"start": {"date-parts": [[2018, 5, 2]], "date-time": "2018-05-02T00:00:00Z", "timestamp": 1525219200000}, "content-version": "vor", "delay-in-days": 0, "URL": "http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/termsAndConditions#vor"}], "content-domain": {"domain": ["onlinelibrary.wiley.com"], "crossmark-restriction": true}, "short-container-title": ["Adv Synth Catal"], "published-print": {"date-parts": [[2018, 6, 15]]}, "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title><jats:p><jats:italic>Alicyclobacillus acidocaldarius</jats:italic>Squalene Hopene Cyclase was evolved to a biocatalyst suitable for (−)‐Ambrox production at industrial scale. One round of random mutagenesis led to the identification of three variants with (<jats:italic>E</jats:italic>,<jats:italic>E</jats:italic>)‐homofarnesol conversion properties improved about 1.5‐ to 10‐fold over that of the wild type enzyme. Eight distinct amino acid mutations were identified overall; only one mutation was at the active site of the enzyme. Each of the three variants contained only two or three mutations over the 631 amino acids of the<jats:italic>Alicyclobacillus acidocaldarius</jats:italic>Squalene Hopene Cyclase polypeptide chain. Mutations responsible for improved (<jats:italic>E</jats:italic>,<jats:italic>E</jats:italic>)‐homofarnesol conversion were identified. Investigations on reaction conditions led to the selection of one variant, with which reaction parameters were optimized towards process‐relevant conditions. A whole cell biotransformation process is presented in which<jats:italic>Escherichia coli</jats:italic>cells producing an improved Squalene Hopene Cyclase variant allows the conversion of 125 g/L (<jats:italic>E</jats:italic>,<jats:italic>E</jats:italic>)‐homofarnesol in ≤72 hours. The developed process for the production of the fragrance ingredient (−)‐Ambrox as Ambrofix® expands the biocatalysis toolbox by setting out a general basis for biocatalytic Squalene Hopene Cyclase cyclization reactions at industrial scale.</jats:p><jats:p><jats:boxed-text content-type=\"graphic\" position=\"anchor\"><jats:graphic xmlns:xlink=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\" mimetype=\"image/png\" position=\"anchor\" specific-use=\"enlarged-web-image\" xlink:href=\"graphic/adsc201800132-toc-0001-m.png\"><jats:alt-text>magnified image</jats:alt-text></jats:graphic></jats:boxed-text></jats:p>", "DOI": "10.1002/adsc.201800132", "type": "journal-article", "created": {"date-parts": [[2018, 4, 17]], "date-time": "2018-04-17T18:22:31Z", "timestamp": 1523989351000}, "page": "2339-2351", "update-policy": "https://doi.org/10.1002/crossmark_policy", "source": "Crossref", "is-referenced-by-count": 50, "title": ["Biocatalytic Process for (−)‐Ambrox Production Using Squalene Hopene Cyclase"], "prefix": "10.1002", "volume": "360", "author": [{"given": "Eric", "family": "Eichhorn", "sequence": "first", "affiliation": [{"name": "Givaudan Schweiz AG Ueberlandstrasse 138 8600 Dübendorf Switzerland"}]}, {"given": "Esther", "family": "Locher", "sequence": "additional", "affiliation": [{"name": "Givaudan Schweiz AG Ueberlandstrasse 138 8600 Dübendorf Switzerland"}]}, {"given": "Sabrina", "family": "Guillemer", "sequence": "additional", "affiliation": [{"name": "Protéus SA 70, allée Graham Bell, Parc Georges Besse 30035 Nîmes Cedex 1 France"}, {"name": "PCAS 2-8 rue de Rouen 78440 Porcheville France"}]}, {"given": "Denis", "family": "Wahler", "sequence": "additional", "affiliation": [{"name": "Protéus SA 70, allée Graham Bell, Parc Georges Besse 30035 Nîmes Cedex 1 France"}, {"name": "Givaudan France SAS 3 rue des Satellites 31400 Toulouse France"}]}, {"given": "Laurent", "family": "Fourage", "sequence": "additional", "affiliation": [{"name": "Protéus SA 70, allée Graham Bell, Parc Georges Besse 30035 Nîmes Cedex 1 France"}